---
title: Past projects
layout: base.njk
eleventyNavigation:
  key: Projects
  order: 4
pagination:
  data: collections.project
  size: 6
  alias: pastProjects
  generatePageOnEmptyData: true
  reverse: true
---

<div class="container">
  <h3>Highlighted projects</h3>

  <p>
    Over the years I have architected, developed and maintained data solutions
    for customers in various industries like e-commerce, finance, manufacturing,
    transport and logistics. These include, but are not limited to any type of:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Inbound order flows (ERP/TMS integration).</li>
    <li>Automating order fulfillment to multi-carrier shipping platforms.</li>
    <li>Custom track & trace flows with automated customer notifications.</li>
    <li>
      Synchronizing product inventory and master data across ERP, PIM and
      marketplaces.
    </li>
    <li>Automating data extraction from PDF.</li>
    <li>Integrating accounting records from specialized apps to ERP.</li>
    <li>Mapping and integrating warehousing movement data.</li>
  </ul>

  <p>Below are some highlighted projects that I enjoyed the most.</p>

  <div class="projects-container">
    {%- for project in pastProjects -%}
    <div class="projectCard">
      <article>
        <hgroup>
          <h3>
            <a href="{{ project.url }}" class="blogPostLinks">{{
              project.data.title
            }}</a>
          </h3>
        </hgroup>
        {% if project.data.thumbnail %}
        <a href="{{ project.url }}" class="blogPostLinks">
          <img
            src="{{ project.data.thumbnail }}"
            alt="{{ project.data.title }} thumbnail"
        /></a>
        {%- endif -%}
      </article>
    </div>
    {%- endfor -%}
  </div>

  {#
  <div id="pagination">
    {% set isFirstPage = (page.url == pagination.href.first) %}
    <button
      onclick="window.location.href='{{ pagination.href.first }}'"
      {%
      if
      isFirstPage
      %}disabled{%
      endif
      %}
    >
      First
    </button>

    {% set previousPage = pagination.href.previous %}

    <button
      onclick="window.location.href='{{ previousPage }}'"
      {%
      if
      not
      previousPage
      %}
      disabled
      {%
      endif
      %}
    >
      Previous
    </button>

    {% set nextPage = pagination.href.next %}

    <button
      onclick="window.location.href='{{ nextPage }}'"
      {%
      if
      not
      nextPage
      %}
      disabled
      {%
      endif
      %}
    >
      Next
    </button>

    {% set isLastPage = (page.url == pagination.href.last) %}
    <button
      onclick="window.location.href='{{ pagination.href.last }}'"
      {%
      if
      isLastPage
      %}disabled{%
      endif
      %}
    >
      Last
    </button>
  </div>
  #}
</div>
